# calc_semantic_ac_clear.numos — AC discards the prior expression: 9+9, AC, 7 == 7.
#
# Phase 8C semantic smoke. NO screenshot, NO golden.
#
# Proves AC fully resets the expression (resetExpression, CalculationApp.cpp:468-470):
# evaluate 9 + 9 (=18), press AC, then type 7 and evaluate. If AC did NOT clear, the
# 7 would append to the old "9+9" AST and the result would not be 7. A clean 7
# confirms the reset.
#
# Run: program --headless --deterministic --script <this> --frames 1400 --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 parse · 3 screenshot · 4 assertion failure.

log "calc_semantic_ac_clear: waiting for launcher"
wait 200
open_app Calculation
wait 60

# First expression (discarded by AC).
key 9
key +
key 9
key ENTER
wait 120

key ac
wait 30

# Fresh expression after AC.
key 7
key ENTER
wait 120

assert_app Calculation
assert_no_error
assert_result 7
log "calc_semantic_ac_clear: PASS (AC clears; 7 == 7)"
